<center><span style="background-color:#ffffff;"><a href="https://syllabus.ict.nitech.ac.jp/search.php">検索 に戻る</a></span><p><table border="1" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="white"><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">授業科目名</div></td><td width="320"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp;Academic EnglishⅡ<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; Academic EnglishⅡ</div></td><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">時間割番号</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">5251</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">担当教員名</div></td><td><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp;Essertier Joseph</div></td><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">実務経験<br>反映科目</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px"></div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">学科・年次</div></td><td colspan="3"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp;工学部第一部  1年次 </div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">科目区分</div></td><td width="320"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp;グローバルコミュニケーション</div></td><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">単位数</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">2</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">時間割</div></td><td align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp;後期 月曜7-8限</div></td><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業形態</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">講義</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業実施方法</div></td><td colspan=3 width="450" align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp&#9745対面&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744オンデマンド&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744同時双方向<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">ディプロマ・ポリシーとの対応</div><div style="margin:10px">&#9744&nbsp1.&nbsp人間，文化，社会を理解し，それらを技術的観点から考察する能力と技術を新しい生活につなぐ強い使命感・責任感，高い倫理観<br>&#9744&nbsp2.&nbsp現象の理解・操作のための数理的基礎知識と科学的素養<br>&#9745&nbsp3.&nbsp国内外の人々と対話できるコミュニケーション力と論理的思考力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（高度工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基盤的な知識・技術とこれによって課題を解決する能力，新たな知識・技術を習得する能力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（創造工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基礎知識と他の分野の知識・技術を関連づけ多面的に見ることで新たな価値を創出する能力<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業の目的・達成目標</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>【授業の目的】</p>
<p>This course emphasizes communicative evaluation and analysis. The overall goal of the course is to improve student ability to understand and produce extended discourse in English, especially in reading and writing contexts. Academic English vocabulary, recognizing and summarizing key points, critical thinking skills, and logical argumentation based on examples and evidence will be emphasized.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span lang="JA">【達成目標】</span></p>
<p>Students will</p>
<p>・acquire greater skills in reading articles in English and knowledge about a variety of current topics,</p>
<p>・enlarge their academic vocabulary and improve their ability to understand the grammatical structure of sentences and paragraphs, and </p>
<p>・gain experience in writing their opinion on current topics</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Week 1: Introduction to course, quick review of 17th century American history and biographical information about Nathaniel Hawthorne</p>
<p>Week 2: Students submit 40 words about their essay topic; Chapter 1 (Hester Prynne's shame)</p>
<p>Week 3: Chapter 2 (Roger Chillingworth's secret)</p>
<p>Week 4: Students submit a title of an article they will read for their essay; Chapter 3 (A fatherless child) </p>
<p>Week 5: Chapter 4 (A man sent by the devil); Quiz 1 on first three chapters of <em>A Scarlet Letter</em> </p>
<p>Week 6: Chapter 5 (A night on the scaffold)</p>
<p>Week 7: Students submit a list of 10 points they will cover in their essay; Chapter 6 (Hester meets the enemy)</p>
<p>Week 8: Quiz 2 on first six chapters of  <em>A Scarlet Letter;</em> Chapter 7 (A walk in the forest)</p>
<p>Week 9: Chapter 8 (Hope for the future)</p>
<p>Week 10: Students submit essay outline</p>
<p>Week 11: Chapter 9 (Escape)</p>
<p>Week 12: Chapter 10 (Hester Prynne's sadness); discussion and review of <em>A Scarlet Letter</em></p>
<p>Week 13: The first half of film version of "The Scarlet Letter" (Demi Moore, 1995)</p>
<p>Week 14: The second half of film</p>
<p>Week 15: Final draft of essay due at beginning of class, discussion of film and book, and Quiz 3 on all chapters of <em>A Scarlet Letter</em></p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>60% of the grade will be determined on the basis of the scores on the three quizzes. These quizzes will include long-answer or essay-style problems. 20% will be based on an essay and other homework, and 20% on the extent of student's participation in discussions.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>Students will be assigned an additional e-learning assignment when necessary. This must be completed by the specified deadline. Other aspects of the grading system will be explained further in class.<br /><br />Based on a maximum score of 100 points possible, grades will be awarded as follows:</p>
<p>S (Excellent) 90-100<br />A (Very good) 80-89<br />B (Good) 70-79<br />C (Pass) 60-69<br />D (Fail) 59 or less</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><div class="OutlineElement Ltr SCXW154735100 BCX9">
<p class="Paragraph SCXW154735100 BCX9"><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">事前学修：教科書や教材の予習，予習課題に取り組む。</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9"> </span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">（</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">120 </span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">分）</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW154735100 BCX9" data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1}"> </span></p>
</div>
<div class="OutlineElement Ltr  BCX9 SCXW154735100">
<p class="Paragraph SCXW154735100 BCX9"><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">事後学修：授業内の講義や解説を理解し</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">，</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">事後課題（レポート，プレゼンテーション，小テストなど）に取り組む。（</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">120</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW154735100 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW154735100 BCX9">分）</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW154735100 BCX9" data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1}"> </span></p>
</div>
<p>Instructions about things to be careful about to receive credit for the course and how to study outside of class will be given during the first class meeting.  <strong>Before</strong> each class, reviewing the textbook can improve in-class comprehension.  <strong>After</strong> class, doing the homework is important. Doing homework on time is essential for group and in-class activities. In order to read and learn about certain topics in science and technology, students may sometimes be directed to consult the Internet with their mobile phones, but mobile phones are not necessary, and mobile communications during class will only be allowed in special circumstances. Learning to work in teams and oral English communication practice is essential, and the best kind of practice is when the student is focused, concentrating on relationships and discussions in the class.</p>
<p>Do the readings, think, participate in discussions in class, share your opinions with your classmates, and enjoy the readings and films.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px"><a href="http://opac.lib.nitech.ac.jp/opc/recordID/catalog.bib/BA87855996" target=_blank>Nathaniel Hawthorne, Oxford Bookworms Library Level 4: The Scarlet Letter (Oxford University Press, 2007), Retold by John Escott<a><br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px">Dictionary<br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Monday 16:20 to 17:20.</p>
